Add: `connectorsCmd.AddCommand(verifyCmd)` wherever the other subcommands are added.

### Step 3: Use typed errors in generic_verify.go

Read `/Users/rejoesudarsan/Projects/nurgesh/internal/connector/generic_verify.go`.

Make these changes:

In `runVerify` function, replace the status code check (currently around line 54):
```go
// Before:
if resp.StatusCode != 200 {
	return "", fmt.Errorf("verify returned %d", resp.StatusCode)
}
// After:
if resp.StatusCode != 200 {
	body, _ := io.ReadAll(resp.Body)
	return "", ClassifyHTTPError(g.def.ID, resp.StatusCode, string(body))
}
```

In `runVerifyAPIKey` function, same change (currently around line 88):
```go
// Before:
if resp.StatusCode != 200 {
	return "", fmt.Errorf("verify returned %d", resp.StatusCode)
}
// After:
if resp.StatusCode != 200 {
	body, _ := io.ReadAll(resp.Body)
	return "", ClassifyHTTPError(g.def.ID, resp.StatusCode, string(body))
}
```

Also improve the token refresh warning in `runVerify` (currently around line 25):
```go
// Before:
fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "  warning: token refresh failed: %v, falling back to original token\n", err)
// After:
fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "  warning: token refresh failed for %s: %v\n  Run `nurge connect %s` if operations fail\n", g.def.ID, err, g.def.ID)
```

Note: `io` is already imported in `generic_verify.go`. `ClassifyHTTPError` is defined in `errors.go` in the same package (just created in Task 1).

### Step 4: Add auth-aware error handling to sync

Read `/Users/rejoesudarsan/Projects/nurgesh/cmd/email/sync.go`.

Change the error handling after `SyncEmails` call (currently around line 41):
```go
// Before:
resp, err := client.SyncEmails(af.Token, lastVersion)
if err != nil {
	return fmt.Errorf("sync failed: %w", err)
}
// After:
resp, err := client.SyncEmails(af.Token, lastVersion)
if err != nil {
	errStr := err.Error()
	if strings.Contains(errStr, "unauthorized") || strings.Contains(errStr, "401") ||
		strings.Contains(errStr, "invalid token") || strings.Contains(errStr, "expired") {
		return fmt.Errorf("sync failed: authentication error.\n  Run `nurge connect gmail` to reconnect\n  Original error: %w", err)
	}
	return fmt.Errorf("sync failed: %w", err)
}
```

